==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sawfish
<hw>Saw"fish`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Any one of several species of elasmobranch fishes of the genus
<gen>Pristis</gen>. They have a sharklike form, but are more nearly
allied to the rays. The flattened and much elongated snout has a row of
stout toothlike structures inserted along each edge, forming a sawlike
organ with which it mutilates or kills its prey.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sawfly</ent>⟦br⟧
